Compound operators/short hand operators:
    Helps us perform same calculations by writing shorter code.
    +=, -=, *=, /=, %=

Type casting:
    Is converting the data from one type to another.

Widening casting (implicit):
byte -> short -> int -> long -> float -> double

Narrowing casting (Explicitly done):
double -> float -> long -> int -> short -> byte

Relational Operators:
    Help us compare things.
    == (equal to)
    != (help us to check if two variables do not contain same information)
    >
    <
    >=
    <=

If else statements:
